> Listfolk,
> 
> I'm going to try something new tomorrow. It may be
> the only time I do it; I
> really don't know yet.
> 
> During the off-season (December thru March), we
> actually have a slow day
> here and there. I'm not being sarcastic; it really
> is an extreme rarity.
> During most of the year, we can barely keep up with
> daily demand (a
> "problem" for which I owe all of you a great bit of
> thanks). But on a rare
> day here and there, everything just lines up to make
> a slow day.  Sales
> volume is seasonally low, no big shipments are due
> to arrive that day, the
> computer didn't crash, no one called in sick, and it
> looks like most of our
> existing orders will make it out the door early in
> the day.  I never know
> when a day like that will happen until the night
> before, at best.
> 
> Since we have "excess capacity" on those days, so to
> speak, it makes good
> business sense to fill that capacity, even if it
> means reducing prices.  So
> that's exactly what I'm going to do.
> 
> Tomorrow (Thursday) will be the first, and maybe
> last, Listmember
> Appreciation Day.  Tomorrow, all listmembers get
> TRIPLE listmember
> discounts. That means 15% off of our discounted
> price, on all items that
> normally qualify for listmember discounts (which is
> most items, with a
> minimum $50 qualifying purchase; details and
> exclusions are recapped below).
> Also, I will allow a 5% listmember discount on Sale
> items (items on the
> website Bargains Page or in the Late Breaking News
> insert sent with our
> catalogs), which normally do not get any listmember
> discount at all.
> 
> This discount will run us dangerously close to
> selling below cost, depending
> on what people order. That's why I'm not sure if
> I'll be able to repeat the
> offer.  I'll have to look closely and make sure that
> I didn't actually LOSE
> money at those prices.  Also, to that end, there
> will be a few rules and
> exclusions, which are listed under this email. 
> Sorry to have to put a few
> conditions on the offer, but please understand that
> at 15% off I'm
> dangerously close to losing money, so I have to be a
> little bit cautious if
> we are to make this work.
> 
> You can order via the website, order desk (by part
> number only), or customer
> service. To get the price, you MUST ask for the
> Triple Discount when
> ordering by phone.  If you order via the phone, the
> discount will be
> calculated right then and there and we can give you
> your new total.  If
> ordering via the website, put TRIPLE DISCOUNT in the
> "comments" section of
> the order form and we will manually adjust the price
> prior to shipping (even
> though the discount will not show up on the
> website). Sale ends tomorrow
> night (at 7 pm via phone and 11 pm via internet,
> eastern time). But it may
> be better to order early as some popular items may
> sell out.
> 
> This would be a good time to stock up on "staples"
> such as filters, tune up
> parts, belts, etc. Think about what you might need
> in the spring and grab it
> now while the price is low. And take a look at the
> website Bargains Page, as
> this will be your only chance to "double dip" and
> get an additional 5% off
> of those Sale prices (since they are normally
> excluded from all further
> discounts).
> 
> If this doesn't kill me too badly, I'll try to
> spring another one on you
> here and there when a slow day comes up. There may
> be one a month, or a few
> a month, or none at all, depending on how things go.
>  We'll see...
